# 1. Database Overview

FleetX uses PostgreSQL as its primary relational database management system (RDBMS).

The database is designed around a shipment-centric logistics model where every operational activity is linked to the movement of customer shipments.

The schema follows Third Normal Form (3NF) to eliminate redundancy while maintaining efficient query performance, scalability, and maintainability.

### Database Objectives

- Maintain a single source of truth.
- Preserve referential integrity.
- Support multi-tenant architecture.
- Enable future AI capabilities.
- Optimize analytical queries.
- Support cloud-native deployments.
- Ensure long-term scalability.

The database stores operational information related to organizations, users, customers, shipments, dispatches, vehicles, drivers, trips, maintenance, fuel, compliance, notifications and reports.

---

# 2. Database Standards

Every table in FleetX follows the standards below.

---

## Primary Keys

- UUID Version 4
- Generated by the backend
- Immutable

Example

```
id UUID PRIMARY KEY
```

---

## Foreign Keys

Every relationship uses UUID foreign keys.

Examples

```
organization_id

shipment_id

vehicle_id

driver_id
```

---

## Naming Convention

### Database Tables

Plural snake_case

Examples

```
organizations

users

shipments

maintenance_records
```

### Columns

All columns use snake_case.

Examples

```
created_at

updated_at

vehicle_number

license_number
```

---

## Audit Columns

Every operational table contains

```
created_at

updated_at

is_active
```

Future versions may include

```
created_by

updated_by

deleted_at
```

---

## Status Fields

Operational entities use ENUM values.

Shipment

- Pending
- Validated
- Assigned
- In Transit
- Delivered
- Cancelled

Vehicle

- Available
- Assigned
- In Transit
- Under Maintenance
- Out of Service

Driver

- Available
- Assigned
- On Leave
- Inactive

Trip

- Planned
- Active
- Delayed
- Completed
- Cancelled

---

## Security Standards

- Passwords are stored only as hashes.
- Sensitive data is encrypted where required.
- Authentication uses JWT.
- Personally identifiable information is minimized.

---

## Indexing Standards

Indexes exist on

- Primary Keys
- Foreign Keys
- Business Identifiers
- Frequently queried timestamps
- Status fields

---

## Scalability Standards

FleetX supports

- Multi-tenancy
- Horizontal scaling
- Read-heavy analytics
- AI workloads
- Cloud deployment

---

# 3. Entity Relationship Overview

FleetX follows a shipment-centric domain model.

```
Organization
│
├── Users
│      └── Roles
│
├── Customers
│      └── Shipments
│               │
│               ▼
│          Dispatches
│          ├── Vehicles
│          └── Drivers
│                 │
│                 ▼
│                Trips
│        ├── Fuel Logs
│        ├── Maintenance Records
│        ├── Compliance Documents
│        ├── Notifications
│        └── Reports
```

---

# 4. Tables

## 4.1 Organization

### Purpose

Represents a logistics company registered on FleetX.

Every operational entity belongs to one organization.

### Table Name

```
organizations
```

### Columns

| Column | Type | Constraints | Description |
|----------|---------|----------------|----------------|
| id | UUID | PK | Organization ID |
| name | VARCHAR(150) | NOT NULL | Company Name |
| legal_name | VARCHAR(200) | NULL | Registered Name |
| registration_number | VARCHAR(100) | UNIQUE | Registration Number |
| tax_number | VARCHAR(100) | NULL | GST / Tax Number |
| email | VARCHAR(150) | UNIQUE | Official Email |
| phone | VARCHAR(20) | NOT NULL | Contact Number |
| website | VARCHAR(255) | NULL | Website |
| address_line_1 | VARCHAR(255) | NOT NULL | Address |
| address_line_2 | VARCHAR(255) | NULL | Address |
| city | VARCHAR(100) | NOT NULL | City |
| state | VARCHAR(100) | NOT NULL | State |
| country | VARCHAR(100) | NOT NULL | Country |
| postal_code | VARCHAR(20) | NOT NULL | Postal Code |
| logo_url | TEXT | NULL | Company Logo |
| timezone | VARCHAR(100) | NOT NULL | Timezone |
| currency | VARCHAR(10) | NOT NULL | Currency |
| subscription_plan | VARCHAR(50) | DEFAULT 'Starter' | SaaS Plan |
| subscription_status | VARCHAR(30) | DEFAULT 'Active' | Subscription Status |
| max_users | INTEGER | DEFAULT 10 | User Limit |
| max_vehicles | INTEGER | DEFAULT 25 | Vehicle Limit |
| is_active | BOOLEAN | DEFAULT TRUE | Status |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | NOT NULL | Created |
| updated_at | TIMESTAMP | NOT NULL | Updated |

### Relationships

Organization has many

- Users
- Customers
- Vehicles
- Drivers
- Shipments
- Trips
- Reports
- Notifications

### Business Rules

- Every operational record belongs to one organization.
- Registration number must be unique.
- Inactive organizations cannot create new records.

